<HEADLINE> Jaguar Kills His Handler at Zoo  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GEORGETOWN, Guyana (AP) -- A jaguar killed his handler, then
escaped from his cage at a zoo in Guyana, police said. The animal
was killed shortly afterward.
</P>
<P>
   The 200-pound jaguar mauled 38-year-old attendant Roxroy Wills
as he was preparing to feed the animal on Tuesday afternoon, police
said. Co-workers at the Georgetown Zoo found him lying near the
open cage. Officials weren't sure if he was attacked inside or
outside the cage.
</P>
<P>
   Police found the jaguar in a nearby shrub and used automatic
rifles to kill it.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is a sad day at the zoo,'' said employee Roger Lackish.
''Nothing like this has ever happened before.''
</P>
<P>
   Co-workers said Wills was a skilled handler, but that he was
feeding the jaguar without the help of an assistant, as zoo rules
require.
</P>
</TEXT>
