<HEADLINE> Two-car crash leaves three friends dead  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FRANKFORT, N.Y. (AP) -- Three people were killed when their car
pulled out onto a highway into the path of an oncoming car, state
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Killed in the two-car crash Tuesday were Raymond Longeretta, 73;
his wife, Mary Longeretta, 70; and their friend, Elaine Biamonte,
62, all of Frankfort. Biamonte and Raymond Longeretta died at the
scene. Mary Longeretta was taken to Little Falls Hospital, where
she died, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   State police said a vehicle operated by Ralph Reed, 66, of
Ilion, was traveling east on Route 5 when the vehicle driven by
Ralph Longeretta suddenly turned onto the road from a florist shop
parking lot.
</P>
<P>
   Reed and his wife suffered minor injuries and were treated at a
Utica hospital and released.
</P>
