<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   He swapped his given name of Prince Rogers Nelson for an
unpronounceable symbol during a protracted contract battle with his
former record label. That led others to dub him ''The Artist
Formerly Known as Prince,'' or ''The Artist,'' for short. Now that
his contract has expired, Prince has reclaimed his name. To
celebrate, he has scheduled a June 13 concert in his hometown of
Minneapolis. Prince says he will continue his fight against what he
perceives as major label domination of the nation's music scene.
Prince, who was born on June 7, 1958, has promised not to ''give up
the store to Forrest Gump accounting firms who think a royalty
check is like a box of chocolates.''
</P>
<P>
   This year's season finale of ''Spin City'' marked the final
appearance of Michael J. Fox on the ABC sitcom. Fox left his
starring role to concentrate on fighting Parkinson's disease, a
progressive neurological disorder. He has launched the Michael J.
Fox Foundation for Parkinson's Research, and says he expects a cure
for the disease by the time he is 50. Fox, who was born on June 9,
1961, was one of the stars of the '80s sitcom ''Family Ties'' and
the ''Back to the Future'' series of films. Fox has insisted that
he isn't giving up show business. But as he told Diane Sawyer on
''20/20'' recently, ''As a performer, I want people to see what I'm
performing, not the dexterity and gymnastics it was taking for me
to perform it.''
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays for June 4-June 10:
</P>
<P>
   June 4: Actor Dennis Weaver is 76. Actor Bruce Dern is 64.
Singer Gordon Waller of Peter and Gordon is 55. Actor Parker
Stevenson is 48. Singer El DeBarge is 39. Actor Scott Wolf (''Party
of Five'') is 32. Actor Noah Wyle (''ER'') is 29.
</P>
<P>
   June 5: Actor Spalding Gray is 59. Singer Laurie Anderson is 53.
Musician Nicko McBrain of Iron Maiden is 46. Saxophonist Kenny G is
44. Actor Mark Wahlberg is 29. Actor Chad Allen (''Dr. Quinn,
Medicine Woman'') is 26.
</P>
<P>
   June 6: Actor Robert Englund (Freddie Krueger) is 51. Actor
Harvey Fierstein is 46. Actress-comedian Sandra Bernhard is 45.
Actress Amanda Pays is 41. Country singer Lisa Brokop is 27.
Actress Staci Keanan (''Step by Step'') is 25.
</P>
<P>
   June 7: Singer Tom Jones is 60. Talk-show host Jenny Jones is
54. Actor Liam Neeson is 48. Singer-musician Prince is 42. Musician
Eric Kretz of Stone Temple Pilots is 34. Actress Larisa Oleynik
(''3rd Rock From the Sun'') is 19.
</P>
<P>
   June 8: Comedian Joan Rivers is 67. Singer Boz Scaggs is 56.
Musician Mick Box of Uriah Heep is 53. Actress Sonia Braga is 50.
Actress Kathy Baker is 50. Actor Griffin Dunne is 45. Musician Nick
Rhodes of Duran Duran is 38. Actress Julianna Margulies (''ER'') is
33. Actor Dan Futterman (''Judging Amy'') is 33. Actress Kelli
Williams (''The Practice'') is 30.
</P>
<P>
   June 9: Comedian Jackie Mason is 66. Actor Michael J. Fox is 39.
Actor Johnny Depp is 37. Actress-singer Gloria Reuben is 35.
Musician Dean Felber of Hootie and the Blowfish is 33. Actress
Natalie Portman (''Where the Heart Is'') is 19.
</P>
<P>
   June 10: Actress Gina Gershon is 38. Actress Jeanne Tripplehorn
is 37. Actress Elisabeth Shue is 37. Model-actress Elizabeth Hurley
is 35. Musician Emma Anderson of Lush is 33. Singer Faith Evans is
27. Singer Lemisha Grinstead of 702 is 22. Actress Leelee Sobieski
is 18.
</P>
</TEXT>
