<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Entertainment Highlights in History  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Entertainment highlights during the week of June
4-10:
<TEXT>
<P>
   50 years ago: Sterling Hayden, Sam Jaffe and Marilyn Monroe
starred in John Huston's ''The Asphalt Jungle.''
</P>
<P>
   30 years ago: The Who performed the rock opera ''Tommy'' at the
Metropolitan Opera House in New York City.
</P>
<P>
   Bob Dylan was awarded an honorary doctorate in music from
Princeton University in Princeton, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   And Godfrey Cambridge starred in ''Cotton Comes to Harlem,''
directed by Ossie Davis.
</P>
<P>
   25 years ago: Elton John's ''Captain Fantastic and the Brown
Dirt Cowboy'' became the first album to enter the U.S. chart at No.
1, where it stayed for seven weeks.
</P>
<P>
   15 years ago: John Travolta became the 1,805th celebrity to
receive a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame. Los Angeles Mayor Tom
Bradley proclaimed the day ''Perfect,'' in honor of Travolta's new
film.
</P>
<P>
   Actor Jeff Bridges, who portrayed a stranded alien explorer in
the movie ''Starman,'' won the Academy of Science Fiction Fantasy
and Horror Films' best actor award. ''Gremlins,'' the story of a
small U.S. town overrun by vicious little monsters, won five of the
academy's 14 honors, including best horror film.
</P>
<P>
   And Anjelica Huston starred in ''Prizzi's Honor,'' directed by
her father John Huston. The film also starred Jack Nicholson and
Kathleen Turner.
</P>
<P>
   10 years ago: It was announced that Charlie Rose, anchor of the
CBS interview series ''Nightwatch,'' was leaving to head
''Personalities,'' a daily interview show for Fox Broadcasting Co.
Rose had headed ''Nightwatch'' since it began in 1984.
</P>
<P>
   And Ricky Van Shelton was chosen entertainer of the year and top
male vocalist at the TNN-Music City News Country Awards show in
Nashville, Tenn. ''I'm shocked, really shocked,'' Shelton said
after the 24th annual fan-voted awards. ''I'm really, totally in
awe.''
</P>
<P>
   Five years ago: Elton John filled the 6,000-seat Kremlin Palace
in Moscow for two performances, 16 years after his first historic
Russian concert tour. Ticket prices ranged from $30 to $200.
Scalpers' prices reached $1,000.
</P>
<P>
   One year ago: Rosie O'Donnell stayed away from the Tony Awards --
and so did most TV viewers. Ratings for Broadway's annual awards
show plummeted after a two-year revival attributed to O'Donnell's
stint as host. Nielsen Media Research said the 1999 show, which had
no host, drew an estimated 9.15 million viewers. That was the
second smallest audience since the show's first telecast in 1974.
</P>
<P>
   And Bob Dylan and Paul Simon kicked off a 30-city summer tour in
Colorado Springs, Colo. They performed hits from their repertoires
and a few duets. It was their first joint tour.
</P>
<P>
   Spoken 10 years ago:
</P>
<P>
   ''I think we need to give black people more credit for their
role in country music.'' -- Entertainer Roger Miller, who gained
fame with his '60s hit ''King of the Road.''
</P>
<P>
   Spoken five years ago:
</P>
<P>
   ''It's scariness that's controllable.'' -- Actress Nicole Kidman,
referring to rock climbing, one of her hobbies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
