<HEADLINE> German TV Plans Nazi Comedy  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   STUTTGART, Germany (AP) -- A German television station is filming
a movie of a kind never before attempted here: a comedy about the
Holocaust.
</P>
<P>
   In the film still under production, a Jew named Harry Geduldig
manages to infiltrate the Nazi party and take the place of
Propaganda Minister Joseph Goebbels in order to free the woman he
loves.
</P>
<P>
   At the climax of the movie, under the working title ''Goebbels
and Geduldig,'' the character ends up in Adolf Hitler's southern
mountain retreat with Goebbels' wife, Magda.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think such a subject also has to be possible today,'' said
lead actor Ulrich Muehe. ''It's already been done abroad.''
</P>
<P>
   To prepare for his role as Goebbels, Muehe said he listened to
original speeches, playing them on the set just before filming
scenes.
</P>
<P>
   The film is to be shown sometime in the fall of 2001 on
Germany's Suedwestrundfunk public station.
</P>
</TEXT>
