<HEADLINE> Tommy Lee Released from Jail  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MALIBU, Calif. (AP) -- Rocker Tommy Lee has been released after
serving five days in the Los Angeles County Jail for violating
parole in a domestic violence case by drinking alcohol.
</P>
<P>
   Malibu Superior Court Judge Lawrence Mira ordered Lee to return
to court for a progress report in September and warned him to stick
to the straight and narrow.
</P>
<P>
   ''(If you) do not commit to sobriety then you're going to come
back to this court and it'll be a very unhappy experience for
you,'' Mira said.
</P>
<P>
   Lee's probation violation occurred as he and estranged wife
Pamela Anderson celebrated on New Year's Eve.
</P>
<P>
   Five months later, after the couple broke up, the actress
reportedly called the district attorney's office and said Lee, the
former drummer for Motley Crue, had violated his probation by
drinking alcohol.
</P>
<P>
   The rock star was charged in February 1998 with spousal abuse,
child abuse and a firearms violation after Anderson called police
from her Malibu home and reported she had been assaulted during an
argument.
</P>
<P>
   Lee pleaded no contest to felony corporal injury to a spouse and
was sentenced to 180 days in jail and three years in state prison,
both of which were suspended, as well as 200 hours of community
service and time in a batterer treatment program.
</P>
</TEXT>
