<HEADLINE> Cuomo-era budget director named to new SUNY economic development post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- A former state budget director who worked in
the Cuomo administration was named Wednesday to a new economic
development position at the State University of New York.
</P>
<P>
   The SUNY Board of Trustees unanimously approved the appointment
of R. Wayne Diesel as the university system's vice chancellor for
business and industry relations.
</P>
<P>
   Diesel will coordinate SUNY's programs and partnerships with
businesses and industries and will serve as a liaison with economic
development agencies. He will also organize a panel of business
leaders who will advise SUNY on business-related programs.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, he will be responsible for overseeing the creation
of a database of research specialties, academic programs and grants
at each of the system's 64 campuses. The database would be
accessible to corporations interested in moving into the state or
retraining existing workers.
</P>
<P>
   Diesel served as state budget director from 1984 to 1988 and was
most recently the president and chief executive officer of the New
York State Credit Union League and Affiliates. The Clifton Park
native has also held senior management positions in several
businesses in the Albany area.
</P>
<P>
   Diesel's job, which is effective immediately, comes with a
$175,000-a-year salary and use of a state vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   SUNY Chancellor Robert King is also a former budget director --
he worked under Gov. George Pataki.
</P>
</TEXT>
