<HEADLINE> Lawyer Sentenced in Murder Scheme  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- A criminal defense lawyer and former federal
probation officer was sentenced Wednesday to eight years in prison
for hiring a hit man to kill two of his former clients.
</P>
<P>
   Frederick R. Ford, 48, pleaded guilty in January to two counts
of planning a murder-for-hire, U.S. Attorney Donald K. Stern said.
</P>
<P>
   Stern said Ford tried to hire a hit man to kill two former
clients who he thought could implicate him in a plot to kidnap a
wealthy marijuana dealer.
</P>
<P>
   The man he tried to hire for $11,000 was an undercover agent.
</P>
<P>
   ''I just want them dead,'' Ford told the agent, according to
court documents. ''I don't want them to suffer.''
</P>
<P>
   Stern said Ford proposed the kidnapping and expected to profit
from the ransom money. He said the investigation into the
kidnapping plot continues.
</P>
