<HEADLINE> AM-NJ--NJ Business Briefs, 1st Ld-Writethru,540  </HEADLINE>
Business news in brief from around New Jersey
<TEXT>
<P>
   WESTAMPTON, N.J. (AP) -- Panasonic AVC American Laboratories
Inc., or PAVCAL, an indirect subsidiary of Japan's Matsushita
Electric Industrial Co. Ltd., has moved its headquarters from
Burlington Township to Westampton.
</P>
<P>
   The facility is Panasonic's largest research and product
development center for digital television and multimedia
technologies in North America. The 42,000-square-foot facility is
double the size of its former headquarters.
</P>
<P>
   PAVCAL employs 100 engineers and a small support staff at the
site, which has been leased for seven years.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   RAHWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Merit Medical Systems Inc., a South Jordan,
Utah-based developer of disposable medical products, said Wednesday
it has purchased the failing Electro-Catheter Corp. for nearly $1
million.
</P>
<P>
   Both companies make various types of catheters, cardiac-pacing
devices and pressure monitoring products.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   EWING, N.J. (AP) -- dotPhoto Inc., a privately held Internet
company that offers a subscriber-based photo sharing service,
announced Wednesday that it has formed an alliance with
Amazingmoms.com.
</P>
<P>
   Under the agreement, Amazingmoms.com will earn 20 percent of
commissions for referring users to the dotPhoto's Web site,
www.dotphoto.com. Amazingmoms.com, which receives more than 20,000
hits per month, will add a link from its Web site to dotPhoto's.
</P>
<P>
   dotPhoto, based in Ewing, offers a photo-sharing portal where
subscribers can post and edit digital photos with sound, text and
voice, organize them into albums and store them in a secure
location that can be accessed by friends and family. It also
produces digital photographic prints.
</P>
<P>
   Roseburg, Ore.-based Newton Creek Studios operates
Amazingmoms.com, a Web site geared for busy families.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- IDT Corp., a telecommunications carrier,
announced Wednesday that it will offer a new prepaid calling card
for its growing base of Spanish-speaking clients.
</P>
<P>
   The ''Aqui y Alla'' card - which means ''Here and There'' in
English - will be available this summer. It will be distributed by
Union Telecard Alliance through its network of more than 100,000
community-based retailers. IDT owns half of Union Telecard, which
sells more than 125 prepaid calling cards.
</P>
<P>
   The card allows customers to receive U.S. rates for
international phone calls through IDT's international Callback
platform, which connects customers to a U.S. dial tone from
anywhere in the world. IDT said the platform, which can be accessed
through a toll-free number, bypasses high rates other countries
typically charge for overseas connections.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   EDISON, N.J. (AP) -- Call Sciences, a privately held company that
offers enhanced wireless services, announced Wednesday that Michael
R. McCoy has been named president.
</P>
<P>
   McCoy, 45, has more than 25 years' experience in the high
technology and telecommunications industries. He previously served
as chief executive of Timeplex International. Prior to that, he
held senior management positions at Nortel Networks, Desktalk
Systems Inc. and LCI International Inc.
</P>
