<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-31 22:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hitchcock Out at Least 8 Weeks  </HEADLINE>
By BERNIE WILSON
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- San Diego Padres opening day starter Sterling
Hitchcock will be out at least eight weeks because of a sprained
ligament in his left elbow.
</P>
<P>
   He might need reconstructive surgery, which would sideline him
for a year or longer.
</P>
<P>
   Hitchcock got a second opinion on Wednesday from Anaheim Angels
Dr. Lewis Yocum, who recommended surgery, Padres trainer Todd
Hutcheson said.
</P>
<P>
   The three options for treating Hitchcock's injury range from
rehabilitation, which would take about eight weeks; arthroscopic
surgery, which could sideline him for a little longer than eight
weeks; or Tommy John reconstructive surgery, Hutcheson said.
</P>
<P>
   Doctors wouldn't know if reconstructive surgery is needed until
they got into the elbow and saw the extent of the damage, Hutcheson
said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Hitch has to make a decision whether he's going to go that
route or have another opinion or have a rehab,'' Hutcheson said.
''Whichever way he goes, it's our job to make sure he gets back as
quickly as possible.''
</P>
<P>
   Surgery was one of the options suggested by the Padres' medical
staff.
</P>
<P>
   Hitchcock, who sprained his ulnar collateral ligament while
pitching against Montreal on Friday night, wasn't available for
comment before Wednesday night's game against Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
   Hitchcock's is the latest in a string of injuries that has
ravaged San Diego's staff. He was put on the 15-day disabled list
Wednesday, joining five other pitchers sidelined by injuries.
Another starter, Woody Williams, had an aneurysm in his right
armpit surgically removed on May 4 and isn't expected back until
around the All-Star break. Brian Boehringer, who opened the season
in the rotation, recently came back from the DL and is pitching in
relief.
</P>
<P>
   Hitchcock, the MVP of San Diego's victory over Atlanta in the
1998 NL Championship Series, is 1-6 with a 4.93 ERA.
</P>
<P>
   Even if Hitchcock picks rehab over surgery, he might still need
to have the ligament repaired later, Hutcheson said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Once the ligament gets stretched, it will heal but it will
never return to its normal length,'' Hutcheson said. ''It will
always be stretched out. The more it stretches, the more the elbow
gaps, and the more it gaps, the more stresses there are on the
other structures, as well.
</P>
<P>
   ''So if he decides not to have surgery, there's a greater chance
that it's going to flare up and he'd need to have something done.''
</P>
<P>
   The Padres promoted two pitchers this week to get them through
the series with Milwaukee. Adam Eaton was brought up from Double-A
Mobile and won his major league debut on Tuesday night, and Rodrigo
Lopez was recalled from Triple-A Las Vegas to start Wednesday
night.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-31-00 2250 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000531.0206 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-31 22:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mud Slide Kills 13 in Guatemala  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- A mudslide triggered by torrential rains
swept through a town in northern Guatemala, killing 13 people and
injuring 24 others, Defense Minister Juan Estrada said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The slide on Tuesday buried 21 homes in Senahu, about 75 miles
northeast of Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities called off the search for more victims Wednesday,
saying everyone had been accounted for.
</P>
<P>
   Estrada said officials won't know the extent of the damage for
at least a week, and their efforts Wednesday were cut short by
another bout of torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
   ''Any further digging and clean-up might have caused further mud
slides,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue workers said the slide left Senahu without drinkable
water and with almost no food, but that government supply trucks
dispatched Wednesday morning had trouble reaching the area because
of impassable roads.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
