<HEADLINE> Ochoa Expected To Miss Three Weeks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI (AP) -- Cincinnati Reds backup outfielder Alex Ochoa
is expected to be sidelined for three weeks as he recovers from an
appendectomy.
</P>
<P>
   Ochoa was taken to a hospital shortly before the Reds' 10-4 loss
to Montreal on Wednesday night. Tests found an inflamed appendix,
and Dr. Timothy Kremchek scheduled surgery overnight.
</P>
<P>
   Kremchek said Ochoa told the club he has had stomach problems
for the last 36 hours. Tests found the problem with the appendix.
</P>
<P>
   ''You don't want it to burst. That's when you really have
problems,'' Kremchek said.
</P>
<P>
   Ochoa is hitting .305 in 33 games, including nine starts in left
field and one in right. He also has gone 3-for-8 as a pinch hitter.
</P>
<P>
   The Reds will decide on his replacement before a game Thursday
night against Montreal.
</P>
<P>
   ''I just found out about it,'' manager Jack McKeon said
following Wednesday's game. ''We'll think about it. We've got all
day. I don't even know who's doing well down there (in Triple-A).''
</P>
</TEXT>
